this wont install. Something wrong with the installer.
Thx for the up anyways..

it will install, only you must extract it using some kind ISO reader or something like that (magicISO is what I use). After you extract it, rename all setup-1.bin into install-1.bin watch out that your numbers at the end of word setup match with the one in the renamed install-"number".bin like

setup-1.bin = install-1.bin
setup-2.bin = install-2.bin
.....etc...
dam...terroncro is right...wish i read his comment before i tried to install...figured it out myself but took over half an hour doing different thing..oh well, it works now...
